    <subsection xml:id="subsec-Multiplying-decimals-by-decimals">
        <title>Multiplying decimals by decimals</title>
        <activity>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    
                </p>
                <p>
                Grade <m>7</m> pupils was given a square garden by the school to plant their  vegetables and each side of the garden measured <m>8.5 m</m>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    1. Draw the shape of the vegetable garden and label its sides.
                </p>
                <p>
                    2. What is the area of the square garden in <m>m</m>? Remember area of a square = side <m>\times</m> side.
                </p>
                <p>
                    3. How did you multiplied the decimals? Share it with your fellow learners.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </activity>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Find the area of the rectagle below.
                </p>
                <image width="40%">
                    <shortdescription>Rectangle image</shortdescription>
                    <latex-image>
                        \begin{tikzpicture}
                                \draw[thick] (0,0) rectangle (4,2);
                                \draw[&lt;-&gt;] (0,-0.3) -- (4,-0.3) node[midway, below] {4 cm};
                                \draw[&lt;-&gt;] (-0.3,0) -- (-0.3,2) node[midway, left] {2 cm};
                        \end{tikzpicture}
                    </latex-image>
                </image>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{ Area of the rectangle } \amp = \text{Length } \times \text{ Width } </mrow>
                        <mrow> \amp = 1.2 \text{ m } \times 0.8 \text{ m}</mrow>
                        <mrow> \amp = (\frac{12}{10} \times \frac{8}{10})\text{m}^2 </mrow>
                        <mrow> \amp = (\frac{96}{100})\text{m}^2 </mrow>
                        <mrow> \amp = 0.96\text{m}^2 </mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Work out: <m>9.132 \times 5.2</m>
                </p>
            </statement>
